---

**PatchMind** is a modular Python CLI tool for Git repositories that generates smart, visual HTML reports.  
It captures **patch-level diffs**, **tree views**, **file history timelines**, **risk scoring**, and more â€” all locally.

No cloud. No bloat. Just clean insight.

---

## ğŸš€ Key Features

- ğŸ” Detects file-level and line-level changes across commits
- ğŸŒ³ Tree-based visualization of modified paths
- ğŸ“… File timeline view with authorship and metadata
- âš ï¸ Risk and impact scoring per file
- ğŸ‘¤ Inline blame summaries
- ğŸ“„ Clean, standalone HTML output
- âš™ï¸ Fully CLI-driven â€” automate in CI/CD

